[4] Brazil (Ceara)
*****
[1] Bangladesh
Date: 25 Nov 2003
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Daily Star 25 Nov 2003 [edited]
<http://www.thedailystar.net/2003/11/25/d3112501044.htm>

7 more die of dengue fever; 337 affected since April [2003]
----------------------
7 more patients died of dengue fever up to 24 Nov 2003 out of a total
of 337 people affected since April [2003] across the country,
officials at the Directorate of Health Services said yesterday.
2 died at Dhaka Shishu Hospital on 12 & 13 Nov 2003, 2 others died at
Dhaka Medical College Hospital on 14 & 16 Nov, one each died at
Chittagong Medical College Hospital on 9 Nov, Suhrawardy Hospital on
22 Nov, and Bangladesh Medical College on 2 Nov 2003.
Out of 337 dengue patients, 256 have been released from various
hospitals, while 81 are under treatment.
A DCC source said that 136 people died of dengue in 2000, some 39 in
2001, and at least 26 last year [2002].
[For one of the world's most populous countries, 337 cases is a very
small number, especially compared with the 3000-6000 reported from
New Delhi alone in neighboring India. - Mod.JW]
