[2] India (Karnataka)
Date: 27 Nov 2003
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Newindpress.com 25 Nov 2003 [edited]
<http://www.newindpress.com/Newsitems.asp?ID=IEK20031125005518&Title=Southern+News+-+Karnataka&Topic=0>

7 dengue cases detected in Raichur
--------------------------
The dreaded dengue disease has been detected in the district. While
Lingsugur taluk reported 5 cases; Raichur and Sindhanur reported one
each.
District Health officer Dr. F.A. Khaji told this reporter that of the
26 samples from Lingsugur sent to the Viral Institute at Bangalore, 5
were found positive for dengue. One sample from Sindhanur had also
tested positive.
Malathion fogging was carried out in dengue-suspected villages of
Lingsugur and Sindhanur taluks and preventive measures introduced, he
said.
******
[3] India (New Delhi)
Date: 27 Nov 2003
From: ProMED <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Delhi Newsline 21 Nov 2003 [edited]
<http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=68635>

[Officially there are] fewer than 2800 confirmed dengue cases among
the 3700 admitted in hospitals with dengue-like symptoms. According
to sources, the number of cases admitted in hospitals from January
[2003] is more than 6000. "The numbers given by the MCD are those
confirmed as dengue by the NICD [National Institute of Communicable
Diseases] from June [2003] onwards, which are about 60 percent of the
total admissions in the hospital. But the total number since the
beginning of this year [2003] are nearly equal to the number reported
since June," said an official in the ministry.
The numbers, however, are much lower than during the 1996 epidemic,
when the figure touched 11 000.
[Byline: Toufiq Rashid]
