[4] Brazil (Ceara)
Date: 25 Nov 2003 00:54:40
From: Marilda Milagres <net_milagres@fclnet.com.br>
Source: Informativo Diario do Nordeste, Brazil 24 Nov 2003 [in
Portuguese, summarized by Mod.JW][edited]
<http://diariodonordeste.globo.com/>

Data from the State Secretary for Health, Ceara, Brazil, show that
the state has recorded its 3rd highest rate for dengue in the last 18
years, with 23 231 cases notified, 279 cases of DHF, and 17 deaths.
To date, 350 000 cases of dengue have been reported in Brazil,
including 42 deaths, 17 of them in Ceara: 9 in Fortaleza [the state
capital], followed by Juazeiro do Norte (2), Crateus (2), Crato (1),
Redencao (1), Caucaia (1) and Assare (1). The 279 cases of DHF were
notified from Fortaleza (164), Juazeiro do Norte (19), Caucaia (12),
& 31 other municipalities. The highest previous total for DHF in the
state was 78 cases in 2001.
